DATA CLOUD
B2C Commerce Connector

You can connect your B2C Commerce instance to a production site and then create a B2C Commerce data stream. You can ingest data from an active protected or unprotected production site. You can’t set up a B2C Commerce connector on a test, sandbox, or non-live production site.

The B2C Commerce Order Bundle deploys mappings to Contact Point type data model objects (DMOs). Identity resolution uses the DMOs to link multiple records in order to combine them into a unified customer profile.

In B2C Commerce, you can create custom attributes with the same name that are case-sensitive, for example, Sustainability and sustainability. Data Cloud doesn’t support case-sensitive field names and converts all field labels to lowercase. If you have case-sensitive custom product attribute names, modify the field names in B2C Commerce before ingesting this data into Data Cloud to avoid any data conflicts.

When you establish a connection between B2C Commerce and Data Cloud, the B2C Commerce Connector ingests 30 days of historical data. For example, if you establish a connection on May 1, the B2C Commerce Connector ingests historical data from April 2 to May 1. From this point forward, the B2C Commerce Connector continues to ingest data.

The B2C Commerce Order Bundle also deploys these data streams:

Product Option
Product Product Option
Product Option Value
Sales Order Product Option Value

If you use these objects within your B2C Commerce instance, map them to custom data model objects in Data Cloud and configure the appropriate data model relationships.

Set Up a B2C Commerce Connection
After you create your Data Cloud instance, you can set up a B2C Commerce Connection. Then you can control the scope of data ingestion from B2C Commerce. The B2C Commerce connector only supports connections to production instances of B2C Commerce.
B2C Commerce Order Bundle Data Mappings
The B2C Commerce Order Bundle shows a sample of the key mappings organized by source objects. You can view all the mappings by reviewing your data streams after the bundle is deployed.
Create a B2C Commerce Data Stream
As a Data Cloud admin, you can use the order bundle to create a data stream to flow data from a B2C Commerce instance. A data bundle creates and maps data streams. The order bundle is a type of data bundle. When you deploy the order bundle, custom attributes for your B2C Commerce Goods Product and Master Product entities are available in Data Cloud to map to a data model object (DMO).
Required Field Mappings to Activate to B2C Commerce
When activating a segment to B2C Commerce, certain data field mappings are required for B2C Commerce and non-B2C Commerce data sources.
